      <abstract>Consider matrix-vector form of nonlinear time-varying discrete
system and its similarity transformations. 

We shall consider a similarity transformation as a canonical
transformation if object's matrix of transformed system is the
Frobenious matrix. We shall consider a similarity transformation
as a canonical transformation if the matrix of closed loop
transformed system is the Frobenious matrix. Sufficient
conditions of existence and explicit form of canonical 
transformation are obtained. 

Theorem 1. If sufficient conditions of canonical
transformation's existence are fulfilled then exists an can be
obtained in explicit form the feed-back vector which provides the
global stability of closed loop system.

Theorem 2. If the conditions of existence of canonical
transformation are fulfilled then exists and can be obtained
in explicit form the feed-back vector for which the closed loop
system is similar to linear time-stationary system.</abstract>
      <title>Canonical Similarity Transformations and Stabilization of Nonlinear Discrete Systems</title>
    </articleInfo>
